Class ZipIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.util.collect.EZIteratorWithNull<java.util.List<java.lang.Object>>
      • com.sri.ai.util.collect.ZipIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<java.util.List<java.lang.Object>>

    @Beta
public class ZipIterator
extends EZIteratorWithNull<java.util.List<java.lang.Object>>
    A ZipIterator is constructed on an array of iterators, and iterates over lists of their next elements until one of them runs out of elements. For example, if given iterators for collections (1,2,3), (a, b, c) and (x, y), it will range over lists (1,a,x) and (2,b,y).
